defaultEssentially the young mind is inquisitive and constructive.  This is witnessed not only in the human race but also in the animal creation;  it is quite delightful to observe the tentat
defaultive, halting attempts of the young hind or calf, rising to its feet, falling, stumbling, straining, tottering, until finally it leaves the ground and takes a few unsteady steps.  With a child, development is very progressive; physically the watchful parent
defaults keep an eye open for anything
default 
defaultthat may hinder or stunt
default its growth, and is continually on the alert for danger, harm, unforeseen hazards.
default&#xa0;
default2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThis watchful care should be a lesson to us and should always mark the parent/child relationship. The child reaching 
defaultmaturity and finally having the privilege of caring for its parent would never forget the natural ties which
default existed
default; the experience always with the elder yet the strength in the younger.
